🔥 Step 2: Replace Code Editor

❌ Remove:

JTextArea codeArea;

✅ Replace with:

import org.fife.ui.rsyntaxtextarea.RSyntaxTextArea;
import org.fife.ui.rsyntaxtextarea.SyntaxConstants;
import org.fife.ui.rtextarea.RTextScrollPane;

private RSyntaxTextArea codeArea;


---

✨ Initialize Editor (IMPORTANT)

Replace codeArea initialization:

codeArea = new RSyntaxTextArea(20, 60);
codeArea.setSyntaxEditingStyle(SyntaxConstants.SYNTAX_STYLE_JAVA);
codeArea.setCodeFoldingEnabled(true);
codeArea.setAntiAliasingEnabled(true);
codeArea.setFont(new Font("Consolas", Font.PLAIN, 14));

// Dark theme feel
codeArea.setBackground(new Color(30, 30, 30));
codeArea.setForeground(new Color(220, 220, 220));
codeArea.setCurrentLineHighlightColor(new Color(50, 50, 50));
codeArea.setCaretColor(Color.WHITE);


---

🧩 Wrap it properly:

RTextScrollPane scrollPane = new RTextScrollPane(codeArea);
scrollPane.setFoldIndicatorEnabled(true);


---

🔁 Replace this line:

codePanel.add(new JScrollPane(codeArea), BorderLayout.CENTER);

👉 WITH:

codePanel.add(scrollPane, BorderLayout.CENTER);


---

😎 Step 3: Add Language Switching (SUPER COOL FEATURE)

Add dropdown:

JComboBox<String> languageBox = new JComboBox<>(
    new String[]{"Java", "SQL", "JSON", "XML"}
);


---

Add this logic:

languageBox.addActionListener(e -> {
    String lang = (String) languageBox.getSelectedItem();

    switch (lang) {
        case "Java":
            codeArea.setSyntaxEditingStyle(SyntaxConstants.SYNTAX_STYLE_JAVA);
            break;
        case "SQL":
            codeArea.setSyntaxEditingStyle(SyntaxConstants.SYNTAX_STYLE_SQL);
            break;
        case "JSON":
            codeArea.setSyntaxEditingStyle(SyntaxConstants.SYNTAX_STYLE_JSON);
            break;
        case "XML":
            codeArea.setSyntaxEditingStyle(SyntaxConstants.SYNTAX_STYLE_XML);
            break;
    }
});


---

Add it to UI:

topPanel.add(languageBox, BorderLayout.WEST);


